# Feeliks Dynamics Website

This repository contains the source code for the Feeliks Dynamics company website.

## Overview

The Feeliks Dynamics website is built to showcase our company's products, services, and expertise in the field of dynamics and control systems. The site is deployed and hosted on Netlify.

## Development

### Prerequisites
- [Jekyll](https://jekyllrb.com/docs/installation/)
- [DecapCMS](https://decapcms.org/docs/jekyll/)

### Setup
1. Clone the repository
2. Install Jekyll and Bundler:
   ```bash
   gem install jekyll bundler
   ```
3. Navigate to the project directory:
   ```bash
   cd feeliks-dynamics-website
   ```
4. Install dependencies:
   ```bash
   bundle install
   ```
5. Start the development server:
   ```bash
   bundle exec jekyll serve
   ```
6. Open your browser and visit `http://localhost:4000` to view the site locally

### Setting up DecapCMS
1. Navigate to `/admin` directory:
   ```bash
   cd admin
   ```
2. Create a `config.yml` file:
   ```bash
   touch config.yml
   ```
3. Configure DecapCMS in `config.yml` with your repository settings and content collections
4. Add the following to your site's `<head>` section:
   ```html
   <script src="https://identity.netlify.com/v1/netlify-identity-widget.js"></script>
   ```
5. Enable Identity service in your Netlify dashboard
6. Configure external providers or email/password authentication
7. Set up Git Gateway in your Netlify dashboard
8. Access the CMS at `yourdomain.com/admin`

Note: Make sure your repository has the necessary permissions set up in Netlify to allow DecapCMS to make changes.
